newsitem.title: EGYPT: Egypt buys 110,000 t Australian wheat at $190/t.
newsitem.headline: Egypt buys 110,000 t Australian wheat at $190/t.

text.p: The Egyptian state's Holding Company for Rice and Flour Mills said it bought 110,000 tonnes of Australian hard wheat from the Australian wheat board at $190.00 a tonne C+F Egyptian Mediterranean ports.
The wheat is in two equal consignments -- 55,000 tonnes for shipment between February 10 and 28 and 55,000 tonnes for shipment between March 1 and 15, a company official said.
